Upload definition models

Upload all models

 

The Conservation Space application administrator is able to load the new definitions using the system.

  1. The user selects from the Administration menu "Manage models".
  2. When the section is opened there is option "Import definitions models".
  3. When the option is selected the user could browse and select the ZIP file to upload in the system.
  4. The user selects Import .
    1. If the definitions are uploaded without errors then a message is displayed to the user "The selected definitions are loaded successfully and the uploaded definitions become active immediately"
    2. If there are errors found in the definitions during the upload, then a screen opens with a list of the errors found, so that the user could review them and make the necessary changes.

 

Upload selected definitions

 

The Conservation Space application administrator is able to load the new definitions using the system.

  1. The user selects from the Administration menu "Manage models".
  2. When the section is opened there is option "Import definitions models".
  3. When the option is selected the user could browse and select one or more object definitions to upload in the system.
  4. The user selects Import .
    1. If the definitions are uploaded without errors then a message is displayed to the user "The selected definitions are loaded successfully and the uploaded definitions become active immediately"
    2. If there are errors found in the definitions during the upload, then a screen opens with a list of the errors found, so that the user could review them and make the necessary changes.
